title: Risk Developer
content:
ABOUT EXODUSPOINT
ExodusPoint Capital, founded in 2017 by Michael Gelband and Hyung Lee, began managing investor capital in 2018. The firm employs a global multi-strategy investment approach, seeking to deliver compelling asymmetric returns by combining complementary liquid strategies managed by experienced investment professionals within a robust risk framework. With a global headcount of over 600 employees and AUM of $13.5B, ExodusPoint brings together an accomplished team with hands-on experience running multi-manager businesses to create an institutional investment management firm. 
OVERVIEW OF THE JOB DESCRIPTION 
The Risk Technology team is looking to hire bright, motivated candidates with a strong background in Computer Science and Mathematics. A strong foundation in Data Structure and Algorithms, expertise in one or more programming languages and database management systems is essential. The candidate will be working closely with the business counterparts in Risk on both the Fixed Income and Equities side. In addition, the candidate would work with the risk tech team to architect and develop robust, low-latency, scalable solutions and help the team support the Risk business.
Responsibilities:

Develop scalable/high performance solutions for low-latency Risk calculations
Liaise with Risk managers to understand the business requirements
Work as a part of a team of strong developers
Support Risk Systems and be a part of End of Day support cycle
Implement Best Practices and ensure a robust Risk Tech Framework

Qualifications:

Bachelorâ€™s degree in Computer Science or related Engineering field
Strong analytical and problem skills
Self-Motivated, passionate, capable of working in a fast-paced environment
Experience in Multi-threading, Client-Server and Distributed computing
Good understanding of various Design Patterns, Algorithms and Data structures
Experience working with SQL

Preferred Requirements:

Mathematical skills, with interest and exposure to quantitative finance
Excellent communication skills
Exposure to AWS/Cloud Technologies
Exposure to PYTHON/Pandas
Exposure to JAVA/Spring/SpringBoot/Microservices framework
Exposure to AI/ML
Experience with Service Oriented Architecture
Exposure to messaging libraries
Good understanding of CI/CD; Unit and Integration testing
Experience working in Linux environment
Exposure to Finance and pricing of basic instruments
Exposure to NoSQL databases
